{
  "doc_id": "59352",
  "text": "The plasma P concentration was determined by direct enzyme immunoassays (EIA) [CITATION_1] . The minimum detectable concentration of the assay was 0.3 ng/mL. The intra-and interassay coefficients of variation were 6.2% and 12.5%, respectively. P was extracted using diethyl ether as described previously [CITATION_2] . The recovery rate of P was 88%. The intra-and interassay coefficients of variation were 6.2% and 9.3%, respectively.",
